Battery
Charging 1 mAh of battery capacity requires 3.6 joules of energy.
1 watt equals 1 joule per second.

Create a class for a battery. The constructor parameters are maximum capacity (mAh) and current charge level (mAh).
Create a command to output the charge percentage.
The charger power is 50 W. Add a command where the number of seconds the charger is connected is specified. Assume all energy is used to charge the battery.
A command allows querying the current charge level.
If charging exceeds the maximum capacity, a separate notification is given. If the charge level reaches 0, a warning is given.
Make the battery model work as a class on a webpage.
Through the user interface, the user can enter the number of seconds for charging and view the current charge level and percentage.
If the battery becomes empty or overcharged, a warning is displayed.